Super convenient located just off the main road of da kao. Had a relatively good experience so returned for seconds. Not disappointed at all, this therapist knew what she was doing. I asked for specific attention to my back and i received a pretty good working over on mu back. It was a 90 min thai massage i had - the place is as ever still cramped, but they had some nice music on this time. The therapist still went through her full routine although i would highly prefer her to work on my back the entire time. Still very good, BUT it annoys me that they still ask for a tip! Come on, i am paying 260k for 90mins, which is over 160k an hour - i am sure not many people earn 160k an hour in HCMC!

Wow! Where do I begin? We came off over 11 hours of flying and of course we will be sore and tender! Got recommended to this massage shop because it was reputable and not dodgy unlike some others. I had a shiatsu massage and my missus had a thai massage - we made it worth our while for 2 hours! My wife highly recommend her thai massage - it was very good, not the best (that goes to the spa at sheraton krabi) but excellent. My massage was also exceptional - the lady worked super hard on my calfs and shoulder / neck area, but did not quite work on my problem area ie lower back. They had a routine they utilise, so for a general massage it is great! For directed massage like my dodgy back, it may not be so great. The room we were in was quite small although there was good air cond. we found that we had problems finding hooks to hang out clothes so that was a problem. The ambience was not very nice but that is ok as i was there for the massage not some fancy smells. All in all, great massage but cramped facilities. The girls had the audacity to ask for a 100K tip at the end although in vietnamese standards they charged like a wounded bull so that was disappointing.

user_titlec: Beautiful spa, good hot stone massage
user_comment: I really like the place, it is very clean and really tastefully decorated. Service is good, fair English and nice smiles. My 75' hot stone massage was excellent if you are looking for a relaxing & smooth experience (400k), my hubbie had a neck and head massage and a foot massage. He was satisfied though not amazed. Prices are fair, slightly lower than the one you can find in renowned spa downtown. They have a program "prepaid 5 services, get one". No pushy with tops at all. I'm be back next week!

I came upon this salon while searching on google for some place to dye my hair. It is $450k for VIP cut and color dye, each time you bleach is $300k. I bleached my hair 3 times and dyed so the total was 1,350k which is about $70 USD. From where i live, this is really cheap but it all comes in pros and cons. I showed my hairstylist the color and style i wanted for my hair but he didnt really listen so maybe a communication barrier? (Because my viet wasnt that good but tbh i wasnt that stupid not to understand the concept of hair). He kept rejecting my idea and suggesting for something more "popular" or "in" nowadays. So i was sitting and looking at colors for less than 3mins and one of the worker/helper walked by and said "if she doesnt pick within 15min, we'll kick her out and let someone sit there" in a very rude tone. So i picked a color and the hair stylist agreed to do so. Saying that itd be 3 - 5 times bleaching and then color. We agreed with the price and went on with thenprocess which was said to be 3 hours but i ended up sitting there for 6 hours lol. My hair was already in a form of ombre bleached color but the stylist wanted to bleach more. The process was long and tiring and all the workers wall by and gave me attitude for my long hair.... lol okay i get that my hair is long but it made me feel very uncomfortable. Anyway, they bleached hair very fast and unprofessionally, leaving an awkward line on the middle of my head because i was going for the ombre effect. The coloring part didnt take that long and the result came out nicely except that my hair was dried and there was an awkward brown line on my head separating from a greyish/green to my black original hair. Overall uncomfortable experience but nice result that i can can live with for a month before recoloring my hair. Would highly recommend this place for those that want to get a simple color dye because its on the nonexpensive side. They also have oil for your hair and recovery process aswell. Came back the next day to wash my hair and for recovery and it was done by another group of workers & they were a lot nicer to be and even braided my hair lol.

My partner and I acquired vouchers for 1hr of foot/body massages at Tokyo moon from a group buy website. We were excited to try out a new spa, but when we came, the manager came out and literally let out a little squeak when we presented her with the vouchers. She then proceeded to inform us that the vouchers were only for locals. This condition was of course not stated anywhere on the vouchers, or the website we bought from. To provide you with more context, I'm Vietnamese Canadian and he is Vietnamese Danish, and we both have Vietnamese passports. Sure, as pastries go, he looks a bit ethnically ambiguous and we communicate with each other in English out of habit. But between the two of us, we've lived in Vietnam for over a decade, so this kind of discrimination was pretty appalling. Let's imagine for a second that it's even okay to charge foreigners a different fee for the service because " they can afford it", in what kind of scenario would it be a win for the spa to straight up tell their guests that they have to pay more because the manager, based on her subjective assessment, decided that they're "foreigners" and will not be issued any promo ? That is just terrible customer service, not to mention downright racist. We were short of showing her scanned pages of our Viet passports when she finally decided that it wasn't necessary (mind you, I had been speaking to her in Vietnamese he whole time). For the rest of our exchange, she alternated between dramatic exhales, uncomfortable smiles, poorly concealed scowls and strange little squeaks. She then informed us that the vouchers we bought did not include tip. Thank you lady, we really appreciate the guilt trip, right after blatant discrimination. The massage was fine, but not mind-blowing enough to off-set the terrible experience we had at the front desk. We tipped our masseuses anyway because we felt that they shouldn't suffer for the manager's behavior, but heck, if you're gonna put your services up on a groupon kind of site, make sure you do it for the right reasons. This could have been an opportunity for you to wow your new customers so that they will come back and pay full price. If you're not getting the volume you expected, take it off that page, but don't treat your customers as if you're doing them some kind of favor. Obviously, we're not coming back or recommending it to anybody.

user_comment: Very basic facilities. Unprofessional staff, Cheeky owner. My boyfriendand I had an Aroma Massage and a Traditional Thai Massage. The aroma was ok, the Thai wasn't good.
